	  src/hugin1/hugin/PreviewPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin1/hugin/TextKillFocusHandler.cpp,
	  src/hugin1/hugin/huginApp.cpp, src/hugin1/hugin/wxPanoCommand.cpp,
	  src/hugin1/hugin/wxPanoCommand.h, src/hugin1/nona_gui/nona_gui.cpp,
	  src/hugin1/stitch_project/hugin_stitch_project.cpp,
	  src/hugin_base/huginapp/ImageCache.cpp: when converting between 16
	  bit unicode and 8 bit strings, use wxConvFileName and wxConvLocal
	  conversions, instead of wxConvCurrent. Fixes an umlaut problem under
	  linux. Might also allow
	  windows users using all characters in the local 8 bit windows
	  codepage for directory/filenames.

