	  mode as well.
	* [r1769] src/Panorama/Panorama.cpp, src/common/Makefile.am,
	  src/common/eig_jacobi.cpp, src/hugin/AssistantPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/PreviewFrame.cpp, src/hugin/PreviewPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/xrc/data/straighten_pano.xpm,
	  src/hugin/xrc/preview_frame.xrc, src/include/PT/PanoCommand.h,
	  src/include/common/Matrix3.h, src/include/common/Vector3.h,
	  src/include/common/eig_jacobi.h, src/include/hugin/PreviewFrame.h:
	  Added "Straighten" button to automatically straigten wavy horizons.
	  Idea based on Matthew Brown's IJCV article.
	  Current does not work with images that were taken in portrait mode,
	  but physically still stored in landscape format.

2006-12-18  dangelo

	* [r1768] src/Panorama/PTOptimise.cpp,
	  src/Panorama/PanoramaMemento.cpp, src/hugin/PreviewPanel.cpp,
	  src/include/PT/PanoramaMemento.h, src/include/hugin/PreviewPanel.h:
	  use m-estimator during autocreate optimisations (requires latest
	  panotools13 svn version),
	  added cross cursor to preview panel
	* [r1767] src/Panorama/PTOptimise.cpp, src/Panorama/Panorama.cpp,
	  src/hugin/AssistantPanel.cpp, src/include/PT/PTOptimise.h,
	  src/include/PT/PanoCommand.h, src/include/PT/Panorama.h: Better
	  heuristics for "Align" function. Now optimizes a,b,c if the control
	  points are distributed well. Also optimizes FOV for 360 degree
	  panoramas, or heavily overlapping images.

