	  vignetting and brightness correction functions
	* [r1437] src/include/vigra_ext/ImageTransforms.h,
	  src/include/vigra_ext/Interpolators.h: use normalized convolution
	  for interpolation kernels.
	  360x180 deg panos can now be remapped without leading to black
	  borders. If the input image doesn't contain an alpha channel,
	  separable convolution is use, should be a bit faster.

