2003-09-14  dangelo

	* [r305] src/hugin/CPEditorPanel.cpp, src/hugin/Events.cpp,
	  src/hugin/ImagesList.cpp, src/hugin/ImagesPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/LensPanel.cpp, src/hugin/List.cpp,
	  src/hugin/MainFrame.cpp, src/hugin/Makefile,
	  src/hugin/OptimizeFrame.cpp, src/hugin/PanoPanel.cpp,
	  src/hugin/huginApp.cpp, src/hugin/xrc/cp_editor_panel.xrc,
	  src/hugin/xrc/images_panel.xrc, src/hugin/xrc/lens_panel.xrc,
	  src/hugin/xrc/pano_panel.xrc, src/hugin/xrc/run_stitcher_frame.xrc,
	  src/include/common/stl_utils.h, src/include/common/utils.h,
	  src/include/hugin/Events.h, src/include/hugin/ImagesList.h,
	  src/include/hugin/ImagesPanel.h, src/include/hugin/LensPanel.h,
	  src/include/hugin/List.h, src/include/hugin/MainFrame.h,
	  src/include/hugin/PanoPanel.h,
	  src/include/hugin/RunOptimizerFrame.h, src/include/hugin/huginApp.h,
	  src/include/hugin/wxPanoCommand.h, src/makefiles/config.mk.tmpl:
	  many changes
	  - rewrote images/lens/pano panel.
	  - xrc cleanup (removed many fixed sizes), there seemed to be many
	  unessecary layers of sizers in images/pano panel.
	  - uses new Panorama model, resulted in massive code size reduction
	  - drawback: not all features of the old code available
	  - List class replaced
	  - split List into a base class and specialized classes for each
	  layout.
	  - completely separate now. no more ugly global variables for
	  communication
	  
	  - many other changes I forgot, I just want to commit the whole thing
	  now ;)
	* [r304] src/tests/Makefile, src/tests/panorama.cpp: many test cases
	  for Panorama and friends added.
	  I'm confident that it works quite well now.
	* [r303] src/Panorama/Makefile, src/Panorama/PanoImage.cpp,
	  src/Panorama/Panorama.cpp, src/Panorama/PanoramaMemento.cpp,
	  src/Panorama/utils.cpp, src/include/PT/PanoCommand.h,
	  src/include/PT/PanoImage.h, src/include/PT/Panorama.h,
	  src/include/PT/PanoramaMemento.h: many changes, list is probably not
	  complete:
	  - removed explicit linking, this affected many functions.
	  - only lens variables can be linked (new class LensVariable)
	  - uses std map & vector to store variables.
	  -> runtime loops over variables etc possible
	  - linking works, for optimize, loading and saving!
	  - many other changes I forgot.
	* [r302] configure: added --debug flag, use it to enable debugging

